name: Email Sent
description: Email sent to a customer. Indicated by Type = 6. Data Source is Pardot.

name: Subscribed To Newsletter
description: Customer submitted the pardot form to subscribe to a newsletter where the detail = "Newsletter Signup". Source: Pardot

name: Opportunity Was Lost
description: Customer became a lost opportunity (based on Salesforce Opportunity Stage: "Closed Lost")

name: Made Payment
description: Customer made a payment on their invoice (could be partial payment)

name: Completed Kira
description: Customer completed Kira Talent (based on Salesforce Opportunity Stage: "Kira Talent Complete")

name: Registered Event
description: Someone registered for an event. Source: Eventbrite.

name: Completed Tech Challenge
description: Customer completed a tech challenge (based on Salesforce Opportunity Stage: "Tech Challenge ... ")

name: Submitted Application
description: Customer submitted an application (bootcamp or continuing education) via Pardot form.

name: Received Acceptance Decision
description: Customer application was approved (based on Salesforce Opportunity Stage: "Application Approved")

name: Opened Email
description: Customer opened an email that was sent to them via pardot

name: Viewed Page
description: Customer viewed a page on the website. Data source segment and snowplow (where the url is not localhost)

name: Received Rejected Decision
description: Customer application was rejected (based on Salesforce Opportunity Stage: "Rejected")

name: Lead Created
description: A new lead was created in Pardot or Salesforce. The pardot lead source is based on the campaign name while the Salesforce lead source is based on the lead source field.

name: Clicked Email
description: Customer clicked a link within an email (often to download course content). Based on the Email Tracker data from Pardot.

name: Opportunity Created
description: Opportunity was created for this customer in salesforce

name: Received Invoice
description: Customer was sent an invoice via Xero. Deleted and voided invoices have been removed.

name: Joined Waitlist
description: Customer was added to the waitlist (based on Salesforce Opportunity Stage: "Wait List")

name: Bounced Email
description: Pardot email was not delivered. Indicated by Type = 13.  Data source: Pardot

name: Downloaded Marketing Content
description: Customer clicked a link in an email to download a file (marketing content). This can be a Course Package, Student Outcomes Report, 101 Report, etc.

name: Submitted Chat Message
description: Someone submitted a message via chat from the website. Source: LiveChat. The ticket source indicates whether or not the ticket was submitted while a live rep was available to respond.

name: Fully Paid Invoice
description: Customer fully completed paying the amount on their invoice (sometimes they split it up into payments, see Made Payment activity). Data source: Xero. All payments where status is paid and fully paid date is set.

name: Scheduled Meeting
description: Customer signed up for a meeting (general meeting or interview) via Calendly.

name: Unsubscribed Email
description: Customer unsubscribed from emails (via Pardot email opt out). Opt out is indicated by type = 12. Data source: Pardot.

name: Registered For Tour
description: Customer signed up for a tour (based on Pardot "Campus Tour" form submission)

name: Identified Visitor
description: For user mapping purposes only. Visitor became identified on the website. Not recommended for use in analysis.

name: Completed Interview
description: Customer completed an interview (based on Salesforce Opportunity Stage: "Interview Completed.")

name: Opportunity Was Won
description: Customer became a won opportunity (based on Salesforce Opportunity Stage: "Closed Won")

name: Viewed Course
description: Customer views a course on the website. Indicated when the URL path equals /course/. Source: Snowplow.
